const layoutProps = {
  toc
};
const MDXLayout = "wrapper"
export default function MDXContent({
  components,
  ...props
}) {
  return <MDXLayout {...layoutProps} {...props} components={components} mdxType="MDXLayout">


    <p>{`Find tutorials, examples and technical articles that will help you to develop with Redis and C.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "getting-started"
    }}>{`Getting Started`}</h2>
    <p>{`In order to use Redis with C, you need a C Redis client.
For your first steps with C and Redis, this article will show how to use the recommended library: `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/redis/hiredis"
      }}>{`hiredis`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <Tabs defaultValue="hiredis" values={[{
      label: 'hiredis',
      value: 'hiredis'
    }]} mdxType="Tabs">
  <TabItem value="hiredis" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`Hiredis is a minimalistic C client library for the Redis database.It is minimalistic because it just adds minimal support for the protocol, but at the same time it uses a high level printf-alike API in order to make it much higher level than otherwise suggested by its minimal code base and the lack of explicit bindings for every Redis command.`}</p>
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "step-1-install-the-pre-requisites"
        }}>{`Step 1. Install the pre-requisites`}</h3>
        <p>{`Version 1.0.0 marks the first stable release of Hiredis.
Follow the below steps to install the pre-requisite packages in order to compile the latest version of hiredis.`}</p>
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{` brew install gcc make
`}</code></pre>
        <p>{`Run the below command to run Redis server`}</p>
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{` redis-server 
`}</code></pre>
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "step-2-install-and-compile-hiredis"
        }}>{`Step 2. Install and compile hiredis`}</h3>
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{` wget https://github.com/redis/hiredis/archive/master.zip
 make
 make install
`}</code></pre>
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "step-3-copy-the-below-c-code"
        }}>{`Step 3. Copy the below C code:`}</h3>
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{` #include <stdio.h>
 #include <stdlib.h>
 #include <string.h>
 #include <hiredis/hiredis.h>

 int main (int argc, char **argv) {
   redisReply *reply;
   redisContext *c;

   c = redisConnect("127.0.0.1", 6381);
   if (c->err) {
       printf("error: %s\\n", c->errstr);
       return 1;
   }

   /* PINGs */
   reply = redisCommand(c,"PING %s", "Hello World");
   printf("RESPONSE: %s\\n", reply->str);
   freeReplyObject(reply);

   redisFree(c);
 }
`}</code></pre>
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "step-4-compile-the-code"
        }}>{`Step 4. Compile the code`}</h3>
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{` gcc redistest.c -o redistest -I /usr/local/include/hiredis -lhiredis
`}</code></pre>
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "step-5-test-the-code"
        }}>{`Step 5. Test the code`}</h3>
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{` ./redistest
 RESPONSE: Hello World
`}</code></pre>
 </TabItem>
    </Tabs>

    <h2 {...{
      "id": "more-c-clients-resources"
    }}>{`More C Clients Resources`}</h2>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://github.com/Nordix/hiredis-cluster"
        }}>{`hiredis-cluster`}</a>{` - C client library for Redis Cluster`}</li>
    </ul>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">
        <p parentName="li"><a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "https://github.com/toymachine/libredis"
          }}>{`libredis`}</a>{` - A C based general low-level PHP extension and client library for Redis, focusing on performance, generality and efficient parallel communication with multiple Redis servers.`}</p>
      </li>
      <li parentName="ul">
        <p parentName="li"><a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "https://github.com/aclisp/hiredispool"
          }}>{`hiredispool`}</a>{` - Provides connection pooling and auto-reconnect for hiredis. It is also minimalistic and easy to do customization.`}</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

;
